
Kcl requires both kinesis and dynamo permissions. It creates dynamo table to store checkpoint and shard information. The dynamo table and other details are add in properties file.

The policy required by kcl is provided in ec2-kcl-policy.json file. This policy should be attached to the ec2 instance role.


Running:

It needs java because kcl uses java internaly.
For Amazon Linux 2023: sudo dnf install java-17-amazon-corretto -y 

In the node app folder run:
node ./node_modules/aws-kcl/bin/kcl-bootstrap \
    --java $(which java) \
    -e \
    -p properties


Kcl needs MultiLanguageDemon written in java to work. The kcl-bootstrap in aws-kcl in node_modules contains the MultiLanguageDemon. 

In the run command, the properties file has the node command which java executes automatically
executableName=node kcl-consumer.js
